317
00:29:04,872 --> 00:29:10,274
I don't think we should be looking
for something we like, Grant.

318
00:29:10,345 --> 00:29:13,312
I don't think we'll ever find that.

319
00:29:14,632 --> 00:29:17,218
I think all we can aspire
to in this situation

320
00:29:17,289 --> 00:29:19,745
is a little bit of grace.

321
00:30:02,121 --> 00:30:05,023
I suppose I'll be
dressed up all the time.

322
00:30:06,697 --> 00:30:11,269
It will be sort of like... in a hotel.

323
00:30:15,530 --> 00:30:16,773
How do I look?

324
00:30:16,842 --> 00:30:17,954
Just like always.

325
00:30:18,025 --> 00:30:19,651
Just as you've always looked.

326
00:30:19,721 --> 00:30:21,576
And how does that look?

327
00:30:23,978 --> 00:30:25,887
Direct and vague...

328
00:30:27,305 --> 00:30:29,477
sweet and ironic.

329
00:30:35,112 --> 00:30:36,869
Is that how I look?

330
00:30:49,385 --> 00:30:51,556
Oh. Remember?

331
00:30:54,217 --> 00:30:56,005
Surprised, Grant?

332
00:30:56,073 --> 00:30:57,480
No, I'm not surprised.

333
00:30:57,545 --> 00:31:00,861
I'm just grateful
you can remember that.

334
00:31:00,937 --> 00:31:03,807
I'm not all gone, Grant. Just...

335
00:31:03,881 --> 00:31:06,118
going...

336
00:31:08,906 --> 00:31:11,327
There are things
I wish would go away.

337
00:31:13,257 --> 00:31:18,210
But won't. You know.
Things we don't talk about.

338
00:31:23,337 --> 00:31:25,858
You never left me.

339
