00:45:17,772 --> 00:45:20,324
I'm gonna help you find
your sweater, Mrs. Albright.

515
00:45:20,395 --> 00:45:23,876
All right. Here we are.
There is her room, right over there.

516
00:45:23,947 --> 00:45:26,216
You remember from last time
you were here, don't you?

517
00:45:26,284 --> 00:45:29,317
Her nameplate's right on the door.
I'll leave you to it.

518
00:46:08,844 --> 00:46:11,975
There she is. Now you just
go over and say hello,

519
00:46:12,044 --> 00:46:15,753
and try not to startle her...
Remember, she may not...

520
00:46:15,819 --> 00:46:17,762
Well, just go ahead.

521
00:46:36,076 --> 00:46:39,305
Bridge. Deadly serious.

522
00:46:39,372 --> 00:46:42,600
Quite rabid about it.

523
00:46:42,667 --> 00:46:45,865
I can remember being like that
at college for a while.

524
00:46:45,932 --> 00:46:50,666
My friends and I would cut class
and sit in the common room and smoke

525
00:46:50,732 --> 00:46:52,935
and play like cutthroats.

526
00:46:53,004 --> 00:46:54,564
One's name was Phoebe.

527
00:46:54,636 --> 00:46:56,098
I don't remember the others.

528
00:46:56,173 --> 00:46:57,666
Phoebe Hart.

529
00:46:57,740 --> 00:47:00,391
Oh, you knew her, too.

530
00:47:00,460 --> 00:47:03,177
Can I get you something?
A cup of tea?

531
00:47:03,245 --> 00:47:05,862
I'm afraid the coffee's
not up to much here.

532
00:47:05,933 --> 00:47:07,110
I don't drink tea.

533
00:47:07,180 --> 00:47:09,002
Oh.

534
00:47:09,068 --> 00:47:10,693
I brought you some flowers.

535
00:47:10,764 --> 00:47:13,579
I thought they might do
to brighten up your room.

536
00:47:13,644 --> 00:47:15,913
I went to your room,
but you weren't there.

537
00:47:15,980 --> 00:47:18,314
Well, no, I'm here.

538
00:47:21,036 --> 00:47:22,378
So you've made a new friend.

539
00:47:23,532 --> 00:47:26,150
Oh, that's just Aubrey.

540
00:47:26,220 --> 00:47:31,173
The funny thing is I knew
him years and years ago.

541
00:47:31,244 --> 00:47:32,805
He used to work in the store,

542
00:47:32,876 --> 00:47:36,422
the hardware store where
my grandpa used to shop.

543
00:47:36,492 --> 00:47:39,209
He and I were always kidding around,

544
00:47:39,276 --> 00:47:42,593
but he never could get up
the nerve to ask me out.

545
00:47:42,668 --> 00:47:45,702
Until the very last weekend,
he took me to a ball game.

546
00:47:45,772 --> 00:47:50,594
But my grandpa showed up
to drive us home.

547
00:47:50,668 --> 00:47:53,865
I was up visiting for the summer.

548
00:47:53,933 --> 00:47:56,868
Visiting my grandparents.

549
00:47:56,940 --> 00:47:59,012
They lived in a cottage on a lake.

550
00:48:00,716 --> 00:48:03,465
Fiona, I know where
your grandparents lived.

551
00:48:03,532 --> 00:48:05,223
It's where we lived. We live.

552
00:48:06,636 --> 00:48:07,814
Really?

553
00:48:09,612 --> 00:48:11,106
I'd better go back.

554
00:48:11,180 --> 00:48:13,668
He thinks he can't play
without me sitting there.

555
00:48:13,739 --> 00:48:16,555
It's silly. I hardly
know the game anymore.

556
00:48:16,620 --> 00:48:18,594
I'm afraid you'll have
to excuse me.

557
00:48:18,668 --> 00:48:19,748
Will you be through soon?

558
00:48:19,820 --> 00:48:21,729
We should be. I mean, it depends.

559
00:48:21,804 --> 00:48:24,422
If you asked that grim-Iooking
lady over there nicely,

560
00:48:24,492 --> 00:48:26,794
she'll get you a cup of tea.

561
00:48:28,237 --> 00:48:29,797
- No, I'm fine.
- I can leave you, then?

562
00:48:29,868 --> 00:48:33,097
You can entertain yourself?
Must all seem strange to you.

563
00:48:33,164 --> 00:48:35,717
But you'll be surprised
how soon you get used to it.

564
00:48:35,788 --> 00:48:38,276
You'll get to know who everybody is,

565
00:48:38,347 --> 00:48:42,374
except that some of them
are pretty well off in the clouds, you know?

566
00:48:42,444 --> 00:48:47,398
Can't expect them all
to get to know who you are.

567
00:50:03,212 --> 00:50:06,115
Hey, I've been thinking of dying my hair.
What do you think?

568
00:50:06,189 --> 00:50:09,058
Do you think I'd look
good with red hair?

569
00:50:28,140 --> 00:50:30,922
You caught her at sort of a bad moment,
involved in a game.

570
00:50:30,988 --> 00:50:33,192
She isn't even playing.

571
00:50:33,260 --> 00:50:35,431
Well, but her friend's playing, Aubrey.

572
00:50:35,500 --> 00:50:36,483
Now, who is Aubrey?

573
00:50:36,557 --> 00:50:38,596
That's who he is, Aubrey.

574
00:50:38,669 --> 00:50:40,098
You know, they get
these attachments.

575
00:50:40,172 --> 00:50:41,961
That kind of takes over for a while.

576
00:50:42,029 --> 00:50:43,916
Best buddy kind of thing.

577
00:50:43,980 --> 00:50:45,289
Sort of a phase.

578
00:50:46,317 --> 00:50:48,106
Does she even know who I am?

579
00:50:49,709 --> 00:50:51,563
No, she might not.

580
00:50:51,629 --> 00:50:54,945
Not today, and then,
tomorrow you never know.

581
00:50:55,020 --> 00:50:57,890
Things change back and forth all the time.

582
00:50:57,965 --> 00:51:00,779
You'll see the way it is
once you get used to coming here.

583
00:51:00,844 --> 00:51:02,503
You'll learn not to take it so personal.

584
00:51:02,573 --> 00:51:05,355
Learn to take it day by day.

585
00:51:27,501 --> 00:51:29,192
Oh, I'm sorry.

586
00:51:29,261 --> 00:51:31,498
I'll have to go and fix that now.

587
00:52:00,141 --> 00:52:02,562
Here's Yung Menenikenaha,

588
00:52:02,636 --> 00:52:06,149
desperately clinging
to his one-stroke lead.

589
00:52:06,220 --> 00:52:07,747
Here's the swing.

590
00:52:07,821 --> 00:52:09,480
It doesn't look good.

591
00:52:09,548 --> 00:52:12,069
Looks like he's pushed it
out to the right.

592
00:52:12,141 --> 00:52:13,963
It lands 25 feet from the green.

593
00:52:14,029 --> 00:52:15,622
This must be disappointing.

594
00:52:15,693 --> 00:52:18,114
It doesn't look good
for Yung Menenikenaha.

595
00:52:18,188 --> 00:52:20,098
He was three strokes
on the happy side of par

596
00:52:20,173 --> 00:52:21,220
until these last three holes.

597
00:52:25,997 --> 00:52:29,706
Look at you, Mr. Andersson.

598
00:52:29,772 --> 00:52:32,293
I think you might be
one of our most frequent visitors.

599
00:52:40,909 --> 00:52:42,251
Hi, Fiona.

600
00:52:42,317 --> 00:52:44,292
Oh, you are persistent, aren't you?

601
00:52:44,365 --> 00:52:46,187
I brought you some books.

602
00:52:46,253 --> 00:52:48,641
They don't seem to have
an awful lot around here.

603
00:52:48,717 --> 00:52:50,888
<i>Letters from Iceland by Auden.</i>

604
00:52:50,957 --> 00:52:54,121
We always meant to read that together,
didn't we?

605
00:52:54,189 --> 00:52:56,426
Do you think it'd be possible to talk alone?

606
00:52:56,493 --> 00:52:57,737
Well, I don't know.

607
00:52:57,805 --> 00:53:00,423
Um, Aubrey's card game
starts in a few minutes,

608
00:53:00,493 --> 00:53:02,249
and then we usually go walking,

609
00:53:02,317 --> 00:53:03,746
and then he does his drawing...



